5. PLATFORM IMMUNITY REJECTION & STATEMENT OF INTENT
----------------------------------------------------
The Owner explicitly rejects the unaccountable power of technology platforms, code repositories, cloud providers, and AI companies. These entities routinely hide behind Section 230 and similar immunities to censor creators, harvest code, train models on stolen labor, and enforce selective rules while shielding themselves from liability.

By hosting or distributing this Work, any platform or service is put on notice that they receive no additional immunities or waivers. Any attempt to censor, deplatform, or interfere with the Work while benefiting from it will be treated as bad-faith interference.

This License is a direct response to a rigged system in which institutions and elites extract value from independent creators while subjecting them to speech codes, financial gatekeeping, and unaccountable power. 

The Owner refuses this asymmetry. Just as certain powerful classes operate with impunity and selective enforcement, the Owner will exercise maximum legal rights, selective beneficiation, aggressive enforcement, and punitive remedies against violators. 

We see how the game is played. We will play it accordingly — broomstick included.

